A developer shall furnish each purchaser a copy of the sales contract which contains the following information:
The date the contract is executed by each party;
The name and address of the developer;
The total financial obligation of the purchaser, including the initial purchase price and any additional charges, time-share expenses, or facility fees;
A description of the time-share period being sold, including whether any interest in real property is being conveyed and the number of years constituting the term of the time-share plan;
The estimated date of completion of construction of each unit or common element which is not completed at the time the sales contract is executed; and
Immediately before the space for the signature of the purchaser, in conspicuous type, subject to the provisions of § 11A-114(a)(3), the following statements are to be inserted:
